cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper deals with the development of a computational approach based on deep convolutional neural networks for breast cancer histology image classification. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also utilizes several deep neural network architectures and gradient boosted trees classifier, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of deep learning models for image classification falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the analysis of histology images, which could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
